data.title: Statement by the Press Secretary: Russian Prime Minister to Visit Washington
data.text:
President Bush welcomes the visit of Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Kasyanov to Washington and New York January 30-February 4, 2002. The President and the Prime Minister will meet on February 4 to discuss a broad agenda of issues, including Russia's economic reforms and the development of U.S.-Russian economic ties.

George W. Bush, Statement by the Press Secretary: Russian Prime Minister to Visit Washington Online by Gerhard Peters and John T. Woolley, The American Presidency Project https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/node/280520
